It is protected by a permission which is not defined in the analysed application. As a result, the protection level of the permission should be checked where it is defined. If it is set to normal or dangerous, a malicious application can request and obtain the permission and interact with the component. If it is set to signature, only applications signed with the same certificate can obtain the permission.

"network_notification_help_combine_body" : "Your AT&T Wi-Fi Gateway has two radio bands and new band steering technology. These features help provide an enhanced Wi-Fi experience and correct common Wi-Fi issues. The radios are as follows:

 		• 2.4GHz: This radio band has 11 channels, can travel farther distances, is the slower band. It is most compatible with older Wi-Fi devices. These radio bands are more susceptible to interference.

 		• 5GHz: This radio band has 25 channels, has a shorter reach, but is the faster band. It is most compatible with newer Wi-Fi devices."

"network_notification_help_combine_body_2" : "Band steering helps direct devices to the optimum signal. It makes sure your devices connect to the appropriate band to get the best Wi-Fi performance. For band steering to work, each radio must have the same Wi-Fi network information. Your 2.4 GHz radio and your 5 GHz radio will have the same name and share the same password. This provides the ability for band steering to:

 		• Reduce network congestion by steering devices to the 5 GHz band which can handle more traffic and bandwidth.

 		• Optimize Wi-Fi network performance by moving devices between the two radio bands as needed and appropriate."

"network_notification_help_disabled_bands_body" : "Your AT&T Residential Gateway has two radio bands for providing Wi-Fi connectivity. Each offers unique advantages. The 5 GHz band offers faster Wi-Fi speeds but has limited reach. The 2.4 GHz offers slower Wi-Fi speeds but has greater reach.

By utilizing both the 2.4 GHz and 5 GHz bands on your AT&T Residential Gateway you can increase the available home Wi-Fi coverage and performance."

"network_notification_help_older_devices_body" : "Older devices can take longer to transmit data which may lower performance for all devices on your home Wi-Fi network.

playstore_details.title: Smart Home Manager
playstore_details.description:
We’re giving you more ways to improve your internet experience with the AT&T Smart Home Manager. As an AT&T Internet customer, you can now personalize and monitor your home network from your smart phone. This app shows a complete view of your home network, and allows you to troubleshoot and manage it from one simple, intuitive interface.
 
Sign in with your AT&T Internet User ID and password to get started!
 
·         Easily view and update your Wi-Fi network name and password.
·         See what is connected to your network and personalize device names.
·         Create Profiles and set Parental Controls to manage your family’s screen time at     home. Go to att.com/shmpc for more info.
·         Test the internet speed to your Wi-Fi gateway.
·         Check your network health, get notified of issues, reboot your Wi-Fi Gateway and more!
 
AT&T Smart Home Manager is available to AT&T Internet service customers with a compatible AT&T Wi-Fi Gateway. Feature availability based on Wi-Fi Gateway model. Limited to home Wi-Fi network.
